definitions.definition: ( ambitransitive ) To cut , dig , scrape , turn , arrange , or clean , with this tool.
examples: to hoe the earth in a garden
Every year, I hoe my garden for aeration.
I always take a shower after I hoe in my garden.

definitions.definition: ( transitive ) To clear from weeds , or to loosen or arrange the earth about, with a hoe.

main_definition: ( ambitransitive ) To cut , dig , scrape , turn , arrange , or clean , with this tool.
